610
00:58:08,359 --> 00:58:11,779 
<i>Christmas is coming!</i>
<i>Have you got your gifts yet?</i>

611
00:58:12,030 --> 00:58:14,908 
<i>No? Look for Malute's Stores!</i>

612
00:58:14,991 --> 00:58:17,827 
<i>Sales at all times!</i>

613
00:58:18,661 --> 00:58:21,664 
<i>We will be giving away</i>
<i>gift cards later on.</i>

614
00:58:21,748 --> 00:58:24,292 
<i>To our beloved audience!</i>

615
00:58:25,001 --> 00:58:29,088 
<i>Meanwhile let's enjoy a song</i>
<i>to warm up our hearts…</i>

616
00:58:33,384 --> 00:58:37,263 
The bathroom floor isn't good
but I think it's easy to fix.

617
00:58:39,766 --> 00:58:42,143 
Girl, there's a ceiling fan.

618
00:58:43,019 --> 00:58:44,020 
Oh no.

619
00:58:45,355 --> 00:58:49,108 
-It scares me a little.
-Stop it. It's fancy.

620
00:58:49,776 --> 00:58:50,818 
Yeah, right.

621
00:58:53,905 --> 00:58:55,823 
Did your dad get angry that day?

622
00:58:59,285 --> 00:59:01,663 
Joana, my dad can get
very annoying with soccer.

623
00:59:04,707 --> 00:59:07,669 
-Do you think I should call him?
-No, leave it alone.

624
00:59:09,128 --> 00:59:11,297 
There are other things involved.

625
00:59:13,925 --> 00:59:15,677 
Your mom didn't like it either.

626
00:59:16,761 --> 00:59:18,054 
No, my mom is all right.

627
00:59:19,806 --> 00:59:21,391 
She looked at me
with a strange expression.

628
00:59:23,268 --> 00:59:24,727 
You had the wrong impression.

629
00:59:30,692 --> 00:59:33,111 
So? Should we close the deal?

630
00:59:36,990 --> 00:59:38,032 
Should we?

631
00:59:42,453 --> 00:59:43,871 
-Baby?
-Yeah?

632
00:59:43,997 --> 00:59:47,083 
-Come here real quick, please.
-Just a second.

633
00:59:52,130 --> 00:59:57,260 
-Tell me.
-I'm going over the bills here.

634
00:59:58,052 --> 01:00:00,388 
Things aren't good.

635
01:00:01,055 --> 01:00:03,558 
It really isn't.
I'm coming from the supermarket now,

636
01:00:03,641 --> 01:00:05,768 
-and it cost me a pretty penny.
-Really?

637
01:00:06,311 --> 01:00:10,106 
-What about work? Nothing?
-No, nothing at all.

638
01:00:10,815 --> 01:00:13,026 
I thought it was gonna get better,
but it just got worse.

639
01:00:13,109 --> 01:00:15,236 
The guys will take
two weeks to come back.

640
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:17,405 
-Beatriz is going on vacation.
-Jeez.

641
01:00:17,488 --> 01:00:20,742 
I asked Claudete for help
but nothing came up.

642
01:00:21,367 --> 01:00:22,744 
It's difficult.

643
01:00:23,870 --> 01:00:26,789 
There's no other way,
we gotta cut some expenses.

644
01:00:27,123 --> 01:00:32,545 
I was thinking, where's the cable bill?
It's very expensive.

645
01:00:32,795 --> 01:00:37,800 
-We could cut the pay per view.
-But, baby. The soccer games.

646
01:00:38,051 --> 01:00:40,595 
It's just a little something.

647
01:00:41,929 --> 01:00:42,930 
A little something?

648
01:00:43,014 --> 01:00:45,099 
The only thing I like
to watch is Cruzeiro's games.

649
01:00:45,183 --> 01:00:47,769 
-And we gonna cut that?
-You need to think about Cruzeiro now?

650
01:00:47,852 --> 01:00:50,772 
Don't mess with Cruzeiro.
Let's think about something else.

651
01:00:52,231 --> 01:00:56,986 
One thing I saw here,
the electricity bill, it's absurd.

652
01:00:57,070 --> 01:00:59,030 
But I save on that, honey.

653
01:00:59,113 --> 01:01:02,200 
I know you do,
but everybody gotta help with that.

654
01:01:02,283 --> 01:01:06,037 
-Nina takes 2 hours to wash her hair.
-But her hair is beautiful.

655
01:01:06,120 --> 01:01:08,790 
I know, she gotta take care of it.
But we need to save.

656
01:01:08,873 --> 01:01:13,544 
That's funny.
When you had your afro, how did you do it?

657
01:01:13,670 --> 01:01:16,089 
Baby, I washed my hair
in the laundry tub,

658
01:01:16,172 --> 01:01:19,175 
and let it dry in the sun.

659
01:01:19,384 --> 01:01:24,639 
-She takes two hours with the hairdryer.
-No, we won't mess with Nina.

660
01:01:24,722 --> 01:01:28,351 
You know what I think?
You should ask your boss for a raise.

661
01:01:28,685 --> 01:01:32,355 
I've tried. They won't give
me a raise just like that.

662
01:01:32,438 --> 01:01:36,109 
Your boss is an ass.
She'll ask you to take care of her cat

663
01:01:36,317 --> 01:01:38,945 
and instead of paying you,
she'll bring you flour from Tchó Tchó.

664
01:01:39,237 --> 01:01:40,738 
Who needs that?

665
01:01:40,822 --> 01:01:43,408 
If I tell you there's no way
it's 'cause there's no way.

666
01:01:43,491 --> 01:01:44,951 
All right, all right.

667
01:01:47,370 --> 01:01:49,038 
But Baby, see…

668
01:01:50,123 --> 01:01:53,000 
Let's just breathe.
It's not the first time, is it?

669
01:01:53,626 --> 01:01:55,712 
-We'll get through this.
-Yes.

670
01:02:09,016 --> 01:02:11,644 
-Thanks, I really liked it.
-Really?

671
01:02:11,811 --> 01:02:13,521 
Then give me a kiss.

672
01:02:15,732 --> 01:02:17,859 
-Merry Christmas.
-To you too.

673
01:02:18,276 --> 01:02:21,612 
I loved it. This one was a star.

674
01:02:23,448 --> 01:02:25,116 
Damn, he could play ball.

675
01:02:26,534 --> 01:02:32,665 
-For you to read on your way to work.
-Thank you, honey. I really liked it.

676
01:02:45,970 --> 01:02:47,138 
Here.

677
01:02:55,605 --> 01:02:59,776 
GOOD FOR ONE NEIL DEGRASSE TYSON LECTURE.

678
01:03:00,610 --> 01:03:02,528 
-You're kidding?
-No,

679
01:03:03,738 --> 01:03:04,989 
I’m serious.

680
01:03:05,156 --> 01:03:06,407 
-You sure?
-Yes.

681
01:03:06,491 --> 01:03:08,910 
-Absolutely? For real?
-Yes. Yes.

682
01:03:09,076 --> 01:03:10,495 
Thank you.

683
01:03:13,831 --> 01:03:15,917 
The card was just to hand you something,

684
01:03:16,167 --> 01:03:18,878 
but I saw the page
for the lecture open on the computer.

685
01:03:19,337 --> 01:03:22,256 
And I noticed you won't stop
watching his videos on YouTube.

